+{"id":"bd-ge1nv","title":"Reject impossible btrfs superblock device accounting","description":"BtrfsSuperblock::parse_superblock_region accepts impossible filesystem-wide device accounting: total_bytes == 0 and bytes_used > total_bytes. Mirror the DEV_ITEM parser boundary by rejecting zero total capacity and bytes_used above total_bytes, add focused regression/proptest coverage, and update parity/coverage docs.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-27T14:31:50.289246931Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T14:40:01.394650877Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T14:40:01.392630710Z","close_reason":"Rejected impossible btrfs superblock accounting at the parser boundary: total_bytes == 0 now fails on total_bytes and bytes_used > total_bytes now fails on bytes_used. Added unit, proptest, and adversarial corpus coverage, updated parity/coverage docs, and refreshed older tests that previously relied on zero-accounting fixtures. Validation passed: cargo fmt --check, git diff --check, UBS touched files, focused ffs-ondisk superblock tests, ffs-ondisk package check, ffs-ondisk package clippy, and workspace check. Workspace clippy was attempted but remains blocked by unrelated dirty ffs-fuse test clippy findings in crates/ffs-fuse/src/lib.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
